#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:3
msgid "TikTok Shop order management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:5
msgid ""
"This guide explains how to manage TikTok Shop orders, inventory, deliveries, "
"and sales reporting within Odoo using the **TikTok Shop Connector**. It "
"covers product catalog mapping, order synchronization, delivery processes, "
"platform fee handling, and sales analysis to streamline social commerce "
"operations across supported regions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:13
msgid ""
"To ensure accurate synchronization, it is crucial to properly map the SKUs "
"between the platforms. The TikTok Shop :guilabel:`Seller SKU` must "
"correspond exactly to the :guilabel:`Internal Reference` of the product or "
"its variant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you are starting a new Odoo database and your products exist only on "
"TikTok Shop, you can import your TikTok Shop product catalog into Odoo. In "
"*TikTok Shop Partner Center*, use the :menuselection:`Bulk action --> Bulk "
"edit products` feature to export your product catalog, including TikTok Shop "
"Item IDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:27
msgid ""
"Then import the exported catalog into Odoo via :menuselection:`Inventory --> "
"Products --> Import`. Map the TikTok Shop Item ID to the :guilabel:`Product "
"external ID` field in Odoo to link your TikTok Shop and Odoo products."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:34
msgid ""
"If you have an existing product catalog in Odoo, map your TikTok Shop "
"listings to these products. Use the :guilabel:`Sync Catalog` button in Odoo "
"to automatically match active products."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:39
msgid ""
"Alternatively, the :guilabel:`Upload in bulk` button in the seller center "
"can be used if products from Odoo need to be synchronized to TikTok."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:43
msgid ""
"Product catalog synchronization is an automated process. Ensure accurate SKU "
"mapping to avoid duplication errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:49
msgid ""
"Orders are automatically fetched from TikTok Shop and synchronized in Odoo "
"at regular intervals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:51
msgid ""
"Synchronization Scope: Only orders with status :guilabel:`AWAITING_SHIPMENT` "
"or :guilabel:`AWAITING_COLLECTION` are fetched, as these require shipping "
"action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:53
msgid ""
"Processing Intervals: Sync orders and Webhooks of order status changes are "
"processed every 5 minutes. Shipping labels are processed every 15 minutes. "
"Inventory is processed every 30 minutes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:55
msgid ""
"Status Updates: When an order is canceled on TikTok Shop, its status updates "
"in Odoo. However, canceling an order in Odoo does not reflect on TikTok Shop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:57
msgid ""
"Customer Creation: For each synchronized order, Odoo uses the buying "
"identifier to search for existing contacts. If none exist, Odoo creates a "
"sales order and a contact."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:59
msgid ""
"Default Products: If a product or delivery carrier isn't found, Odoo uses a "
"default product or carrier found by :guilabel:`Internal Reference` or name, "
"respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:70
msgid ""
"To synchronize an order whose status hasn't changed since the last "
"synchronization, navigate to :menuselection:`Sales --> Configuration --> "
"Shops` and click the target TikTok Shop. Modify the :guilabel:`Last Order "
"Synchronization` date to a date prior to the order's last status change. "
"Finally, click the :guilabel:`Sync Orders` button to trigger immediate "
"synchronization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:78
msgid ""
"For :abbr:`FBM (Fulfilled By Merchant)` orders, the **TikTok Shop "
"Connector** creates a picking in the :menuselection:`Inventory` app, a sales "
"order, and a customer record, upon synchronization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:81
msgid ""
"Arrange Shipment: Confirm the picking in Odoo, then navigate to *TikTok Shop "
"Partner Center* and arrange shipment to generate the shipping label and "
"tracking number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:83
msgid ""
"Fetch Shipping Label: Odoo retrieves the shipping label and tracking number "
"automatically on orders with TikTok status of 'Awaiting Collection', "
"attaching them to the corresponding delivery order. If PDF generation fails, "
"a link to the label is provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:86
msgid ""
"Validate Stock Out: Validate the stock movement in Odoo to update inventory "
"levels and confirm the order has left the warehouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:90
msgid "TikTok Shop delivery statuses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:92
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Awaiting Shipment`: The order is ready for shipment arrangement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:93
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Awaiting Collection`: The seller has arranged shipment and "
"received a tracking number from the logistics provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:95
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Shipped`: The parcel has been dropped off or picked up by the "
"logistics provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:96
msgid ":guilabel:`Cancelled`: The order has been canceled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:97
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Pickup Failed`: The logistics provider failed to pick up the "
"parcel and the seller must rearrange shipment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:101
msgid ""
"TikTok Shop requires a tracking reference for each delivery. If the carrier "
"doesn't provide one automatically, set it manually in *TikTok Shop Partner "
"Center*. Check supported logistics providers for the region."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:108
msgid ""
"TikTok Shop orders are automatically created in Odoo as sales orders in the "
"**Sales app**. Shipment can be arranged in *TikTok Shop Partner Center*, "
"including choosing a logistics provider and generating a shipping label. "
"Odoo imports any shipping labels and tracking numbers and associates them "
"with the sales order. Stock movements are confirmed in Odoo to reduce "
"inventory levels. Enabling synchronizing inventory in shop settings pushes "
"stock levels to TikTok shop in order to prevent overselling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:118
msgid ""
"Due to TikTok Shop's policy of not sharing customer email addresses, "
"invoices cannot be sent directly from Odoo. Instead, invoices can be "
"generated in Odoo and manually uploaded to *TikTok Shop Partner "
"Center*. :ref:`Register a bank journal <accounting-setup-bank>` (e.g., "
"\"TikTok Payments\") with a suspense account. Since TikTok shop processes "
"batch payments, all invoices linked to a payment in Odoo can be processed "
"by :ref:`creating a batch payment <accounting/batch/creation>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:126
msgid "Analyzing TikTok Shop sales with Odoo's reporting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/sales/sales/tiktok_connector/manage.rst:128
msgid ""
"Odoo's dashboard consolidates sales data from all channels. To analyze "
"TikTok Shop sales specifically, set up sales teams. Go "
"to :menuselection:`Sales --> Configuration --> Shops` and assign a dedicated "
"sales team to each TikTok Shop for isolated reporting. Use the dashboard "
"filters to view sales data for the assigned TikTok sales team."
msgstr ""

